==English==

===Etymology===
From Greek words "anti" = "[[against]]" and "thesis" = "[[position]]".

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-antithesis.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''antithesis'''
# a [[proposition]] that is the [[diametric]] [[opposite]] of some other proposition.

